3\. Access Control Matrix by Document Type and Role

This matrix maps document access permissions to the platform\'s 9-role
RBAC model. Permissions follow a default-deny model with tenant
isolation enforced at the database layer via PostgreSQL Row-Level
Security. Each permission level is defined as follows:

**FULL:** Create, read, update, delete, share, manage permissions

**MANAGE:** Create, read, update, share (no delete, no permission
changes)

**EDIT:** Create, read, update (no delete, no share)

**VIEW:** Read-only access

**OWN:** Access only to documents related to own property/account

**SCOPED:** Access limited to specific work-order or engagement context

**NONE:** No access

3.1 Access Matrix: Governing & Legal Documents

Governing documents are broadly accessible for viewing since they define
the rules all members must follow. Edit access is restricted to board
leadership and management roles.

