5.5 Template System Requirements

**Template Editor:** WYSIWYG editor with merge field insertion via
dropdown/autocomplete. Preview with sample data before sending. HTML and
PDF output from same template.

**Versioning:** Each template version is numbered and dated. HOAs can
customize platform-provided templates; customizations are preserved
across platform updates. Revert to any prior version.

**Multi-Language:** Templates support translation variants. Default:
English. Phase 2: Spanish, Chinese, Vietnamese, Korean (top WA
languages). Merge fields populate in the selected language where
applicable.

**Branding:** Per-HOA branding: logo, colors, fonts, contact
information. Consistent header/footer across all generated documents.
Custom letterhead support.

**Conditional Logic:** Templates support if/then blocks (e.g., include
EV deemed-approval language only for EV applications). Show/hide
sections based on data conditions.

**Delivery Integration:** Templates feed directly into delivery
pipelines: email (SendGrid), physical mail (Lob), portal notification,
SMS (Twilio). Track delivery status per template instance.

6\. Technical Architecture Recommendations

6.1 Storage Architecture

Primary Document Storage: Amazon S3

**Encryption:** Server-side encryption with AWS KMS (SSE-KMS). AES-256.
Per-tenant encryption keys for maximum isolation. Enable S3 Object Lock
for compliance-critical documents (governing docs, legal records) to
prevent deletion during retention period.

**Bucket Strategy:** Single bucket per environment (dev/staging/prod)
with prefix-based tenant isolation:
s3://hoa-platform-prod/{tenant_id}/documents/{category}/{year}/{document_id}.
Enable S3 Versioning for immutable audit trail at the storage layer.
Lifecycle policies: transition to S3 Intelligent-Tiering after 90 days;
Glacier Deep Archive for documents past retention period awaiting
disposal confirmation.

**Access Control:** All S3 access via presigned URLs generated by the
application layer. No direct bucket access. URLs expire after 15 minutes
(configurable). CloudFront distribution for document preview delivery
with signed cookies for authenticated sessions.

**File Size Limits:** Default maximum: 100MB per file. Configurable per
tenant (up to 500MB for reserve studies, plat maps). Multipart upload
for files over 10MB. Client-side file type validation before upload;
server-side re-validation.

Supported File Formats

The system must support the following formats, organized by rendering
capability:

**Native Preview (in-browser):** PDF, JPG, JPEG, PNG, GIF, WEBP, SVG,
TXT, CSV, MD, HTML

**Converted Preview (rendered via LibreOffice/Gotenberg):** DOCX, XLSX,
PPTX, DOC, XLS, PPT, RTF, ODT, ODS

**Stored Only (download to view):** DWG, DXF, TIFF, MP4, MOV, AVI, ZIP,
EML, MSG

**OCR Candidates:** Scanned PDFs (no text layer), TIFF, JPG, PNG

6.2 Document Processing Pipeline

The document processing pipeline runs asynchronously to avoid blocking
the user experience. It uses an event-driven architecture with SQS
queues and Lambda functions (or ECS Fargate tasks for long-running
processes).

**Queue 1: Ingest:** Triggered on upload. Virus scan (ClamAV Lambda),
format validation, metadata extraction. Average processing time: 2--5
seconds.

**Queue 2: Transform:** Document preview generation via Gotenberg
(open-source, Docker-based document converter). Thumbnail generation
(first page, 200x280px). PDF/A conversion for long-term archival.
Average processing time: 5--30 seconds.

**Queue 3: OCR:** Amazon Textract for scanned documents. 300 DPI
rasterization for optimal accuracy. Page-level text extraction with
confidence scoring. Output: searchable PDF overlay + extracted text
JSON. Average processing time: 3--8 seconds per page.

**Queue 4: Index:** Push extracted text, metadata, and classification to
OpenSearch. Page-level indexing with document backreferences.
Incremental indexing (only re-index when content or metadata changes).
Average processing time: 1--3 seconds.

**Dead Letter Queue:** Failed processing jobs retry 3 times with
exponential backoff. After 3 failures, move to DLQ for manual review.
Alert operations team. Common failures: corrupt files,
password-protected PDFs, unsupported formats.

6.3 Search Architecture

Search Engine: Amazon OpenSearch Service

OpenSearch (AWS-managed Elasticsearch fork) provides the full-text
search backbone. It offers managed infrastructure, automatic scaling,
fine-grained access control, and built-in integration with the AWS
ecosystem.

**Index Design:** Primary index: documents---one document per OpenSearch
document with nested page objects. Fields: title (keyword + text, boost
3x), category (keyword), document_type (keyword), tags (keyword array),
body_text (text, boost 1x), page_text (nested, text), created_date
(date), modified_date (date), retention_class (keyword), tenant_id
(keyword, used for index-level filtering), author (keyword), status
(keyword), ocr_confidence (float).

**Search Features:** BM25 full-text search with field boosting. Fuzzy
matching for typo tolerance. Phrase matching for exact quotes. Filters:
document type, category, date range, author, status, retention class,
tags. Highlighting: return matched text snippets with highlighted search
terms. Pagination with cursor-based scrolling for large result sets.

**Semantic Search (Phase 2):** Vector embeddings via Amazon Bedrock or
OpenAI for conceptual search. Use case: searching for \'landscaping
rules\' also returns documents about \'yard maintenance standards.\'
Hybrid scoring: 70% BM25 + 30% vector similarity.

**Saved Searches:** Users can save and name search queries. Board
members can create shared saved searches visible to the board. Alert
subscriptions: notify when new documents match a saved search.

6.4 OCR Pipeline

**Primary Engine:** Amazon Textract for production workloads. Tight S3 +
Lambda integration. Mature async processing. Good table and key-value
pair detection for financial documents. Cost: approximately \$1.50 per
1,000 pages.

**Fallback / Cost Optimization:** Tesseract 5.x (open-source) for batch
processing of low-priority documents. PaddleOCR for any CJK-language
documents (if multi-language communities require it). Run on ECS Fargate
Spot instances for cost efficiency.

**Pre-Processing:** Pre-crop margins before OCR (improves confidence
from \~0.81 to \~0.86 per testing data). 300 DPI rasterization (sweet
spot---600 DPI bloats storage with minimal accuracy gain). Deskew and
denoise scanned images. Language detection to route to appropriate OCR
engine.

**Quality Metrics:** Store per-page OCR confidence scores. Flag pages
below 0.75 confidence for human review. Dashboard showing OCR processing
queue depth, average confidence, and failure rate.

6.5 PDF Generation Engine

**Technology:** Gotenberg (open-source, Docker-based) for HTML-to-PDF
conversion. Puppeteer/Chromium for complex rendered PDFs (financial
reports, board packets). WeasyPrint as lightweight alternative for
simple template-based PDFs.

**Use Cases:** Template-based document generation (violation notices,
ARC letters, meeting minutes). Financial report packets (P&L, balance
sheet, budget vs. actual, bundled with cover page and TOC). Annual
meeting packets (compiled multi-document packages). Resale certificates
and disclosure packets. Assessment invoices and statements.

**Requirements:** PDF/A output for archival compliance. Digital
signature embedding for e-signed documents. Watermarking (DRAFT,
CONFIDENTIAL, COPY). Barcode/QR code embedding for document tracking.
Consistent rendering across viewing platforms.

6.6 Document Preview Rendering

**Architecture:** CloudFront CDN serves preview renditions. PDF.js for
in-browser PDF rendering (no server-side rendering needed). Image
previews served as optimized WebP with progressive loading. Office
documents (DOCX, XLSX, PPTX) converted to PDF on upload for preview;
originals preserved for download.

**Performance Targets:** Preview load time: under 2 seconds for
documents up to 50 pages. Thumbnail load time: under 500ms. Progressive
loading for large documents (render first page immediately, load
remaining pages in background).

6.7 E-Signature Integration

**Recommended Primary:** DocuSeal (open-source, self-hosted). Zero
per-signature cost. Full API with webhooks. Templates, embedded signing,
audit trails. Self-hosted ensures data sovereignty and no vendor
dependency.

**Recommended Secondary:** Dropbox Sign (HelloSign) API for users who
prefer a managed service. Clean developer documentation. Competitive
pricing for SaaS integration. SOC 2 and GDPR compliant.

**Integration Pattern:** API-first: generate signing request from
template with merge fields populated. Embedded signing: signer completes
within the platform (no redirect). Webhook callbacks on status changes
(sent, viewed, signed, completed, declined). Completed documents
automatically filed in the appropriate document category with
certificate of completion attached. Audit trail: signer IP, timestamp,
authentication method stored per signature.

6.8 Multi-Tenant Document Isolation

**Storage Layer:** S3 prefix isolation: /{tenant_id}/documents/. No
cross-tenant key access possible via IAM policies. Separate KMS keys per
tenant for encryption at rest.

**Database Layer:** PostgreSQL Row-Level Security (RLS) on all document
metadata tables. tenant_id column on every table. RLS policies enforce
that queries only return rows matching the authenticated tenant.
Connection-level tenant context set via SET app.current_tenant.

**Search Layer:** OpenSearch index filtered by tenant_id on every query.
Application layer enforces tenant context before any search request. No
cross-tenant search possible.

**Application Layer:** JWT tokens include tenant_id. Every API request
validates tenant context. Document URLs include tenant-scoped presigned
tokens. API middleware rejects any request where the document\'s
tenant_id does not match the authenticated user\'s tenant.

6.9 Backup and Disaster Recovery

**S3:** Cross-region replication enabled (primary: us-west-2, replica:
us-east-1). Versioning enabled---accidental deletions recoverable.
99.999999999% (11 nines) durability.

**Database:** RDS automated backups with 35-day retention. Point-in-time
recovery. Cross-region read replica for disaster recovery. RPO: 5
minutes. RTO: 1 hour.

**OpenSearch:** Automated snapshots to S3 daily. Manual snapshot before
any index migration. Index can be rebuilt from database + S3 sources if
needed (recovery time: hours, not data loss).

**Compliance:** Document disposal requires explicit authorization
workflow---no automated deletion of documents within retention period.
Disposal certificates generated and retained for 7 years. Cryptographic
erasure for documents past retention: delete KMS key renders all
encrypted objects irrecoverable.

7\. Feature Specification

7.1 Document Organization

Folder Structure

The default folder structure is auto-created per HOA tenant and reflects
the 12-category taxonomy. Users can create custom sub-folders within any
category. Folders support drag-and-drop reorganization. Documents can
exist in one canonical folder location with shortcuts/links from other
locations.

**Default Top-Level Folders:** Governing Documents, Financial Records,
Meeting Documents, Compliance & Enforcement, Architectural Review,
Insurance & Risk, Vendor & Contracts, Legal, Communications,
Administrative, Elections & Voting, Resale & Transfer

**Auto-Generated Sub-Folders:** Financial Records auto-creates per-year
sub-folders (e.g., Financial Records / 2026 / Statements). Meeting
Documents auto-creates per-meeting folders (e.g., Meeting Documents /
2026-03-15 Annual Meeting). Violations auto-creates per-case folders
(e.g., Compliance / V-2026-0042 / \[all case documents\]).

Metadata Schema

Every document carries a standardized metadata schema with both
system-managed and user-editable fields:

**System-Managed:** document_id (UUID), tenant_id, file_name, file_size,
file_type (MIME), upload_date, uploader_id, storage_path (S3 key),
checksum (SHA-256), ocr_confidence (if applicable), version_number,
version_status (Current/Draft/Superseded/Rejected), retention_class
(Permanent/7-Year/1-Year/Duration-Based/Custom), retention_expiry_date
(calculated), processing_status (Pending/Processing/Complete/Failed)

**User-Editable:** title (display name), description, document_type
(from taxonomy enum), category (from taxonomy enum), tags (free-text
array), effective_date, expiration_date, related_entity_type (property,
owner, vendor, violation, arc_case, meeting), related_entity_id,
access_level_override (if different from category default), notes

**Naming Convention:** System enforces:
{YYYY-MM-DD}\_{Document_Type}\_{Description}.{ext}. Example:
2026-03-15_Board_Minutes_Regular_Meeting.pdf. Auto-rename on upload with
user-editable display name.

7.2 Search Functionality

**Search Bar:** Unified search bar accessible from any screen.
Auto-suggest as user types (document titles, tags, recent searches).
Search scope selector: All Documents, Current Folder, Specific Category.

**Full-Text Search:** Search within document content (extracted text +
OCR output). Highlight matched terms in document preview. Search result
cards show: title, category, date, relevance score, snippet with
highlighted match.

**Filters:** Document type (multi-select from taxonomy), Category, Date
range (created, modified, effective), Author/Uploader, Tags, Status
(Current, Draft, Archived, Superseded), Retention class, Related entity
(property address, owner name, violation number, ARC case number), File
type (PDF, DOCX, image, etc.), OCR confidence threshold.

**Advanced Search:** Boolean operators (AND, OR, NOT), Phrase matching
(quoted strings), Wildcard search, Field-specific search (title:budget,
tag:reserve), Date-relative search (modified:last_30_days).

**Search Results:** Default sort: relevance score. Alternative sorts:
date (newest/oldest), title (A-Z), file size. Result grouping by
category or document type. Bulk actions from search results: download,
share, move, tag, export list.

7.3 Version Control

**Versioned Document Types:** All governing documents, rules, policies,
architectural guidelines, templates, financial reports, budgets, reserve
studies, meeting minutes (draft to approved).

**Version Numbering:** Semantic: major.minor. Major: formal amendments,
new editions (requires approval workflow). Minor: corrections,
formatting updates. System auto-increments minor; major requires
explicit user action.

**Version History UI:** Timeline view showing all versions with: version
number, date, author, status, change description. Side-by-side diff for
text-based documents. One-click revert to any prior version (creates new
version, does not delete history).

**Diff Engine:** Text-based diff for DOCX and TXT (using delta
algorithm). PDF diff via visual overlay comparison. Highlighted
additions (green), deletions (red), modifications (yellow). Export diff
as annotated PDF.

**Concurrent Edit Prevention:** Optimistic locking for web-form-based
edits. Pessimistic locking (check-out/check-in) for file-based
documents. Lock timeout: 4 hours default, configurable. Lock override by
Board President or Super Admin with audit log entry.

7.4 Audit Trail

**Events Tracked:** Document created, Document viewed, Document
downloaded, Document edited (new version), Document shared (with whom,
method), Document deleted (soft delete), Document archived, Document
restored, Permissions changed, Metadata modified, E-signature
initiated/completed, Search performed (query logged), Export performed,
Retention policy applied/modified.

**Audit Record Fields:** event_id, timestamp, actor_id, actor_role,
tenant_id, document_id, event_type, event_details (JSON), ip_address,
user_agent.

**Retention:** Audit logs retained for minimum 7 years. Immutable---no
edit or delete capability. Exportable to CSV/PDF for legal discovery or
compliance audits. Filterable by: date range, actor, document, event
type.

**Compliance Reporting:** Pre-built reports: Documents accessed by
user/date range, Documents approaching retention expiry, Documents
overdue for review/update, Records request response time metrics,
E-signature completion rates.

7.5 Retention Management

**Auto-Classification:** Documents auto-assigned retention class based
on document type from taxonomy. Override capability for Board President
and Super Admin with audit log.

**Retention Countdown:** Dashboard widget showing documents approaching
retention expiry (30/60/90-day warnings). Automated alerts to designated
retention officer.

**Disposal Workflow:** Documents past retention period flagged for
review. Disposal requires explicit approval from Board President or
designated officer. System generates disposal certificate: list of
documents, retention policy applied, disposal date, authorizing officer.
Cryptographic erasure: delete S3 objects and purge from search index.
Disposal certificates retained for 7 years.

**Legal Hold:** Attorney or Board President can place legal hold on any
document or category. Legal hold overrides retention expiry---documents
cannot be disposed while hold is active. Track holds with: reason, date
placed, placed by, associated matter.

7.6 Compliance Features

**Multi-State Compliance Engine:** Configurable per-tenant compliance
rules. Parameters: response deadline for records requests, copy fee
calculation formula, penalty structure, exempt record categories.
Default: Washington State (RCW 64.38 + WUCIOA). Phase 2: top 10 HOA
states (FL, CA, TX, AZ, NV, CO, IL, NC, VA, WA).

**Compliance Dashboard:** Records request SLA tracking with deadline
countdown. Retention expiry calendar. Insurance certificate expiration
alerts. Contract renewal date tracking. Reserve study update reminders
(annual update, 3-year visual inspection for WA). Secretary of State
filing reminders. Board training compliance tracker.

**Address Confidentiality Program:** Auto-redaction of ACP participant
addresses from any document shared with non-board members. ACP flag on
owner profile---system-enforced, cannot be bypassed. Applies to: owner
roster downloads, meeting attendance lists, any document containing
owner addresses.

8\. Competitive Analysis: Document Management in HOA Platforms

This section synthesizes findings from analysis of 22 HOA management
platforms, focusing specifically on their document management
capabilities and shortcomings.

8.1 Market-Wide Findings

No platform in the self-managed HOA tier provides true compliance-grade
document management. The enterprise tier (Vantaca, CINC, AppFolio,
Buildium) offers stronger features but at price points and complexity
levels inappropriate for volunteer boards. The specific gaps that
represent differentiation opportunities for this platform are:

**Version Control:** Only HOA Start adds version control among Tier 3
platforms. PayHOA has none. No platform offers
governing-document-specific amendment tracking with side-by-side diff
capability.

**Retention Management:** No self-managed platform tracks document
retention schedules, automates expiration alerts, or provides disposal
workflows. This is universally absent.

**Compliance Automation:** No platform automates state-specific records
request deadlines, tracks penalty exposure, or provides compliance
calendars for document-related statutory obligations.

**OCR and Search:** HOA Start limits search to titles only. PayHOA
offers basic folder-based storage with search. No self-managed platform
provides full-text search across document content or OCR for scanned
documents.

**E-Signatures:** PayHOA lacks e-signatures entirely. Most Tier 3
platforms lack this feature. Users must rely on external tools
(DocuSign, etc.) with no integration.

**Template Sophistication:** PayHOA\'s template builder is rated
\'Basic\' with users reporting formatting difficulties. No platform
offers compliance-aware templates with statutory language
auto-insertion.

**AI-Powered Classification:** Only CINC\'s Cephai+ (enterprise) offers
AI-generated board packets. No self-managed platform uses AI for
document classification, metadata extraction, or content summarization.

8.2 Platform-Specific Findings

**PayHOA (incumbent):** Strengths: unlimited storage, drag-and-drop,
folder structure, encryption, per-document/folder/user permissions, CC&R
hosting, financial report packet generation, HomeWiseDocs resale
integration. Weaknesses: no versioning, no e-signatures, basic template
builder, no full-text search, no OCR, no retention tracking, no
compliance automation, no meeting-specific document workflows.

**HOA Start:** Adds version control and nested security measures. Limits
search to titles only. \$39/month flat pricing is aggressive.

**HOALife:** Property-level document files integrated with violations
and requests. Strong linking between documents and operational records.
GPS-enabled inspection photos.

**Buildium:** Compliance management with audit trails. Enterprise-grade
but \$174+/month and designed for professional managers.

**CINC Systems / Cephai+:** AI-generated board packets with executive
summaries. Auto-processes 31,000+ invoices. Enterprise-only
(\$250+/month).

**Vantaca / HOAi:** Most advanced AI: autonomous invoice processing,
automated ARC form review with compliance checking. Enterprise-only with
custom pricing.

8.3 Differentiation Strategy

This platform should deliver enterprise-grade document management at
self-managed pricing by combining: (1) compliance-aware retention and
records request management that no competitor offers at any tier, (2)
full-text search with OCR that only enterprise platforms currently
provide, (3) version control with governing-document-specific amendment
tracking, (4) integrated e-signatures via open-source DocuSeal (zero
per-signature cost advantage over DocuSign-dependent competitors), (5)
AI-assisted document classification and template population, and (6)
template system with statutory-language auto-insertion that eliminates
the legal risk of non-compliant notices.

9\. Implementation Roadmap

The document management system should be built in three phases, with
each phase delivering standalone value while laying groundwork for
subsequent phases.

9.1 Phase 1: Foundation (Weeks 1--12)

Core document storage, organization, and access control. This phase
replaces PayHOA\'s existing document management with parity-plus
features.

**S3 storage backend:** Upload, download, organize, folder structure,
tenant isolation, encryption

**Document metadata schema:** Full taxonomy implementation, tagging,
categorization

**RBAC integration:** Per-document and per-folder permissions mapped to
9-role model

**Basic search:** Title, filename, tag, and metadata-based search. No
full-text yet.

**Document preview:** In-browser PDF and image rendering. Office doc
conversion to PDF for preview.

**Version control:** Check-in/check-out, version history, status labels

**Audit trail:** All document actions logged, immutable, exportable

**Template system (basic):** 10 core templates with merge fields:
meeting notices, violation notices, ARC letters, assessment invoices

9.2 Phase 2: Intelligence (Weeks 13--24)

Search depth, OCR, compliance automation, and e-signatures. This phase
establishes the competitive moat.

**Full-text search:** OpenSearch integration, content indexing, field
boosting, highlighting

**OCR pipeline:** Amazon Textract integration, scanned document
processing, searchable PDF generation

**Retention management:** Auto-classification, countdown timers,
expiration alerts, disposal workflows

**Records request workflow:** Intake, acknowledgment, deadline tracking,
exemption review, fee calculation, delivery tracking

**E-signature integration:** DocuSeal self-hosted. Embedded signing.
Template integration.

**Compliance dashboard:** Multi-state records request deadlines, penalty
exposure tracking, insurance/contract expiration alerts

**Template system (full):** All 25+ templates, conditional logic,
multi-channel delivery integration, branding customization

9.3 Phase 3: AI and Advanced Features (Weeks 25--36)

AI-powered capabilities and advanced document workflows. This phase
delivers features currently available only in \$250+/month enterprise
platforms.

**AI document classification:** Auto-categorize uploaded documents by
type and suggest metadata

**AI content extraction:** Extract key data points from financial
statements, invoices, contracts

**Semantic search:** Vector embeddings for conceptual search beyond
keyword matching

**Board packet auto-assembly:** AI-compiled meeting packets with
executive summaries

**Document diff with AI summary:** Natural-language description of
changes between governing document versions

**Smart redaction:** AI-assisted PII detection and redaction for records
request fulfillment

**Multi-language templates:** Spanish, Chinese, Vietnamese, Korean
translation variants

**Advanced analytics:** Document usage patterns, search analytics,
compliance scoring

